First, let's find A△B. The symmetric difference of two sets A and B is the set of elements which are in either of the sets but not in their intersection. So, A△B = (A∪B) - (A∩B).

A∪B = {1,2,3,4} (union of A and B)
A∩B = {2,3} (intersection of A and B)

A△B = {1,2,3,4} - {2,3} = {1,4}

Now, let's find (A△B)△A and A△(B△A).

1. (A△B)△A = ({1,4}△{1,2,3})
To find the symmetric difference, we will find the union and intersection of the sets.

({1,4}∪{1,2,3}) = {1,2,3,4}
({1,4}∩{1,2,3}) = {1}

So, (A△B)△A = {1,2,3,4} - {1} = {2,3,4}

2. A△(B△A) = {1,2,3}△({1,4})
Again, let's find the union and intersection of the sets.

({1,2,3}∪{1,4}) = {1,2,3,4}
({1,2,3}∩{1,4}) = {1}

So, A△(B△A) = {1,2,3,4} - {1} = {2,3,4}

Thus, (A△B)△A = A△(B△A) = {2,3,4}.
